{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Hold a binding referendum before reducing the current voting age",
        "additional_details": "The potential social and national impact of a reduced voting age (which we feel is not justifiable on the simplistic basis that 16 yr olds pay tax - most don't!) could be significant and we believe it should NOT be left to MPs. Whilst part of their manifesto, I believe the Government\u2019s total vote in 2024 is NOT a sufficient mandate to proceed solely on a Parliamentary vote.",
        "background": "We believe the Government\u2019s decision to reduce the voting age to 16 should be based on a formal, binding referendum of the current electorate.",
